column5: A rainy day here on OFC  Well it’s raining again so I’m inside and dry  This means I’m not in my boat drowning a worm, minnow or fly  In my younger days I’d be out there getting drenched  But now I’ve got memories and a thirst to be quenched  I gaze out the window as my boat fills with water  At times I think I should be leading worms to their slaughter  I could be out there catchin pike, walleyes or trout  But the skies letting go so I just sit here and pout  What keeps me goin and my brain keeps a ticken  The next time I have me a real nice bush chicken  Bushguy
Can't wait to see the painting
Just can't wash that bush chicken out of your head....
Well it hasn't rained a drop here in Hamilton Terrence, but none the less I'm stuck inside too.  Been working on a few custom rod donations, one will show up at Lakair in the near future.
She's chuckin here in the valley boys
Stopped raining by 930 and the clouds parted at 11. The sun shone and the fish co-operated.
Been raining here since 4:30pm yesterday afternoon and hasn't quit once. Thank God I spent 9 hours cutting grass yesterday or I'd be buggered...
